reviews.reviewText: This is so so so cute! It's exactly what I was looking for! A great price and easy to put together. I love that the top has a USB port and 2 spots to plug in anything. Its just the right size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value, super cute
reviews.reviewText: I really liked how cute it is. I wish the particle board was stronger was it was damaged upon arrival. Building was pretty difficult! its impossible to do the whole project with that tiny little screw handle thing. It turned my hands red and i had to take many breaks. 2 of the screws ended up stripping but i managed to replace the worse one and use a pliers to get the better one flush w the surface. Luckily i was able to fit the right allan bit for my drill and finish the project. I decided to keep the back panel off for cord managment and im so glad i did. Its the perfect size for my laptop and i got some matching floating shelves for my glasses too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functional and Stylish!
reviews.reviewText: We needed two nightstands for our bedroom, and didn't have much space to fit them in. These saved the day! They're small, but perfect to fit two in smaller spaces and surprisingly fit all that we need inside! I've got all my books/journal in the drawer, a small clip lamp and my phone and charger on top, along with a water bottle and sleeping mask. I still have room below in a basket for a tissue box, Chapstick and lotion! Add on the charger ports and it's a grand slam! Wonderful design!

reviews.reviewTitle: Soho or boho or just broke
reviews.reviewText: This is a great little night stand just like your budget. But hey fake it till you make it. Color true to picture, drawer is a little meh but otherwise it looks nice
Love this nightstand. A bit smaller than I thought but still like it very much:)

As other reviewers have mentioned, the screw holes are far too small for the large screws included in the kit. After trying in vain for about 40 minutes to get the screws in for the first step of assembly, I gave up and packed it back up and will be returning it. I’m no stranger to putting together flatpack furniture and this was only the first step! They give you an Allan key to put these screws in, which is a joke. Maybe if I’d had a high powered drill it would have worked but even with multiple screwdrivers I couldn’t get them in. A total waste of time and effort.

I like the colour of the nightstand, it goes very well with the decor already in my bedroom. As far as the assembly; the first couple of instructions took a couple of tries but the remaining I would say was user friendly. The nightstand is quite smaller than I expected, if I had know how small it would have been I most likely would have opted in for a bigger one. Overall the craftsmanship is similar to that of an ikea table. It is decent material, that should last you quite awhile but again ,you get exactly what you pay for.
